room.name: Is the word in the list template

custom-block.s: is the word %txt in the list %txt

block-definition.s: is the word %'word' in the list %'list'
block-definition.comment: Takes a word and a list of words as input and reports true if the second contains the first (otherwise reports false). Also returns false if no word is provided or if the empty list is provided. You should be able to fill in the blanks (and sometimes the blanks inside these extra blocks) to create a working version of the program with only these blocks, but you may add more if you wish.
